						<div class="postbody">Here's <a href="http://forum.6502.org/viewtopic.php?p=23964#p23964" class="postlink">code</a> (6502.org) for a simple parabolic approximation of a sine wave.<br /><br />If you run two instances 90 degrees apart that will give you something like a circle.<br /><br />Of course, it's incremental not random access.<br /><br />There's an <a href="http://atariage.com/forums/topic/263420-plot-a-circle/#entry3723112" class="postlink">example here</a> (AtariAge) in Batari Basic.</div>

